    "id": "eFIP_Corpus_PMC2175300_S15",
    "text": "From these results , we suggest that the C-terminal region of the DNA-binding domain of FOXO proteins is crucial for effective DNA binding and that the sequential events of PKB-induced phosphorylation , the binding of 14-3-3 protein , and CBP-induced acetylation in this region can inhibit binding of the C-terminus to DNA .",
